	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				5 of 10 with no deaths in one hour today. Woot!<BR>
<BR>
I thought I'd give my perspective on this as I am on a PvP server (Sullon) which should make this more difficult. Apart from not having any wolf form (no druids on team evil), it isn't. I would suggest waiting until you get your first round of gates at 19, as that makes for a lot less running.<BR>
<BR>
Neriak - Duh, I'm a dark elf. :) If you aren't evil, well... good luck. Leave everything in the bank, invis and run in. If I were good or nuet, I would do this one after getting gate at 4th. Have a high level friend invis you outside of the city, and run in, gate out. I can't think of any other way unless you are really high level as this is the major hub of evil.<BR>
<BR>
Oasis - No problem here, invis and swim out towards the island. I started in the SE corner as that is easiest. There were only 2 goblins in the tower and they were both non-casters that couldn't see through invis. I guess I got lucky on this one. Since evil OWNS the desert, good/nuet should try zoning in halfway between the cliffs and the water from Northern Ro. Dodge SG's until you get to the lake, either side of the zone will have lots of evils that will raise the red flag, but the middle is rarely populated. Heck, those that are there are too busy dodging SG's to con you.<BR>
<BR>
Dagnor's - very easy to find, still had enduring breath from Oasis. I would definitely advise doing this and Unrest during non-peak hours if you are on the evil team. Even so, since good/nuet think they own these, they will rarely have see invis up. I had all chat channels on and no one even bothered to announce my arrival.<BR>
<BR>
Unrest - Appart from being a good/nuet controlled zone, this was very simple. If you are on team evil, please feel free to shout insults as you gate away. : )<BR>
<BR>
Lake Rathe - Ok, this one scared the bejezus out of me. It is a LONG tunnel and visibility is poor. Enduring breath or equivelant is MANDATORY, regardless of swim skill. I would stay high in the tunnel as there are several gobs that will be sitting on the floor (it is a big tunnel as well as long, so just swim over them). The good news is, unlike Oasis, this rod spawns within reach of the window. My tower had 2 non-casters and 1 see invis caster on the top floor, but by simply floating past the appropriate window and grabbing it, I was ok. Be careful where you pause to gate out, since there are gobs on the floor of the main hall, I would suggest swimming a ways back down the tunnel until you find a clear spot. Above all, keep that invis up! Factionally, this should be no problem as there are few people in this zone, and they aren't likely to cross your path while in the water.<BR>
<BR>
I'll stop back in with a look at the later 5 rods (from Sullon's perspective) when I get them tonight.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
			<td nowrap bgcolor="#808080" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_silver.gif">	
			<a href="/US_Admin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=471604"><img border="0" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
