	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				While doing this quest, if you can get wolf form, *get* it. It helps with the rods in oasis, rathe, and lguk. They're easy. It doesn't hurt to have a 20+ mage give you some stones that cast enduring breath. Most will do it for nothing, because it isn't a big deal for them, and they're no rent.<BR>
<BR>
As for the sharks in Erud's Crossing, I was warned while doing it that a level 50 shark swam there, although all of the sharks that I conned around the rod were green to me.<BR>
<BR>
For the Qeynos rod, facing the Qeynos main ent, go left until you see a small section of the wall that is covered in vines. It's false. As soon as you swim into the pool, you'll zone into the Aquaduct system. I went invis here, although everything I conned was green. Just go left and straight at every cross section. You'll drop at one point, but the dmg you'll take is minimal. The sharks were green, and as soon as I grabbed the rod I gated out.<BR>
<BR>
Hope that helps clarify things a little.<BR>
=================================<BR>
Caear dae'Shir &lt;Bringers of Fire&gt;<BR>
Server: Bristlebane<BR>
Level: 24
				</font>
			</td>

